&lt;p&gt;BAND 6 ROLE OPHTHALMOLOGY THEATRES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FULL TIME PERMANENT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for us to appoint a new Band 6 within our Ophthalmic Theatres. Currently we have 4 Ophthalmic Theatres providing excellent care to both Adult and Paediatric patients. Including elective and emergency cases based at Queens Medical Centre within Nottingham University hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to demonstrate the ability to work flexibly and have a high level of self-management, including time management, prioritisation and organisational skills and a commitment to the Ophthalmology Team. While maintaining the Trust values and behaviours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All persons appointed to the post are required to hold registration with their appropriate professional Regulatory Body and to comply with their professional code of conduct. Evidence of on-going registration will be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Support Division would especially welcome applications from BAME colleagues who are currently underrepresented at this level&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours of work are 37.5, working 07:30- 18:00 Monday-Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameViv FulfordEmail addressvivienne.fulford@nuh.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
